column5: Man I wish i could have gone..... Im sick of winter already and it doesnt arrive for another week!!!!!

I have to be brief but just wanted to give the quick update that at least one musky was caught at the G2G on the upper niagara! In all the years I've gone, we've never got anything on the closing week-end but we finally broke that OFC goose egg with a respectable musky. I couldn't make it to the dinner, but I hope to hear other successful reports soon. I'll post more info and a pic in a day or two.
But Rizzo who was it let us know   let the cat out of the bag will ya.,
Well it sure wasn't us!
Congrats, was pretty cold out there today.
OH no don't tell me Pete(Biteme) had an episode of contaminating the Lake and it shut the fishing down.  I want to see pics of very cold people
We may have to attend next year eh Mike???
You mean real men.Not a wimmpy guy who put his boat away when it was still in the + temps.
Yeah!... what's up with that eh?

Our winter is alot tougher than yours too much snow here.Alot more snow here. Like to see you get the boat lauched here.  BTW I am not getting a full roof with enclosure cause I am not as old as you  Its minus 15 here and like minus 25 with the windchill
Okay, $20 it was Lew     Any takers???  Joey
Is that aimed at me? Just because I set myself on fire to stay warm doesn't mean I'm a wimp!! ; -Brian
That must of been one hell of a fire 2000 sqr feet of survival suit
Ill take that bet!!..................
I wouldn't want to bet against Lew  , I'll vote for Lord Tundra'n if he made it. Heard he was gonna attend.
If it is Lew I hope he made an acception he normaly doesn't take alot of Muskie pics.

well if you guys got one, I know of 2 others   , and I think we got a pic of the one coming in your boat.  One of the two was caught by walleyemen in my boat today  , and for the record...we lost 3     Walleyemen lost 2 at the side of the boat...too green to net em, soon as they both got to the side of the boat..they opened thier mouth's and out popped his bait  ..and I lost a nice one too....all 4 fish hooked in the same area...hmmmmm wish my wife didn't have to work all day tommorrow....I got half a mind to go again.  anyways not tyinbg up this thread, I will add more later too, just want to say it was a great day out there for a cold December fishin day, and it was a day spent with a bunch of first class people all the way...thanks for joining me in my boat today too walleyemen
I got a feeling it was lew that caught that ski..... will just have to see a little later on  Leechman

I had a great day out there,and was even better getting to meet all of board members that attended,,,and also want to thank jwl for getting there early and clearing up the ramp and also for setting us up with a great place to eat afterwards!!  Hope next year will be a   better outcome for my boat!!,,lol  :clapping:

it was great joint effort at the ramps...good job 3-4 of us brought salt/sand for sure...we dumped 2 bags on it and started smashin it up before the whole gang got there, and it still took a bit  and yepper, I figured that would be a good place to stop and fuel up after a day on the water..they feed ya good there for your buck.  Next year Sonny??...I am trying to weasel my way into somehow going tommorrow  , we hooked 4  ,one in the boat   ..by walleyemen...on my lure none the less  I cracked the code by changing game plans a little bit last part of the day..too bad I didn't start like that cuz I was gonna    My stubourness to wrk one small area paid off, I am glad I helped him get into that fish...cool to be part of the first G2G where there was fish caught.  Count me in next season for sure
Mikey Mikey Mikey You big Yellow Mask wearing Pussy didnt see your sorry butt out there with your warp drive tiller turd what up with that!!!!!

well we're back in Barrie now, glad to hear you had so much action Jack! The fish have had lockjaw any other year we've been down there that late. That's great you guys had 4 fish on! Thank you to those who got the ramp clear, I think all the launching went smooth other than boats being frozen to trailers!
Too bad I had to back out, but I need to be at home right now.  Glad to see you were hot into the action Jack.
No pike were harmed in the making of this outing on the Niagara !!  There were a few boated today !
